@database "Ling"
@author Alfonso Ranieri

@Node "Main" "Ling"

    @{u}@{b}Ling@{ub}@{uu}
    Written by Alfonso Ranieri


    @{" Author  " LINK "Author" } @{"  WRID  " LINK "WRID  "}
    @{" Usage   " LINK "Usage"  } @{" Window " LINK "Window"}
    @{" Changes " LINK "Changes"}

   ------------------------------------------------------------


    Ling is robust accounts manager.
    It is based on a BlowFish CBC algorithm.

    Ling lets you store all your accounts in an unique file so
    that, instead of remembering many passwords, or to use the
    same password for everything (Scaring!!!), you just need
    to remember the Ling database one.

    Ling may result sometime annoying, because of it timeouts
    after a certain period of inactivity or because of it
    requests often the database password to perform some
    operation, but all that is related to security reasons.

    Note that both the database password and the accounts
    passwords are always kept in memory encrypted and they are
    exposed only when needed.

@EndNode

