@Node "WRID" "Ling - Warning, Requirements, Installation and Distribution"

  @{b}Warning, Requirements, Installation and Distribution@{ub}


    @{u}Warning@{uu}
    THIS SOFTWARE AND INFORMATION ARE PROVIDED "AS IS". ALL USE
    IS AT YOUR OWN RISK, AND NO LIABILITY OR RESPONSIBILITY IS
    ASSUMED. NO WARRANTIES ARE MADE.

    @{u}Requirements@{uu}
    MorphOS 1.4 or higher.

    @{u}Installation@{uu}
    Use the installer script.

    @{u}Distribution@{uu}
    Ling is distributed in the Public Domain.

    Ling uses the following third part stuff:

    - NList classes by Gilles Masson (http://sourceforge.net/projects/nlist-classes)
    - Textinput MUI classes by Oliver Wagner (http://www.vapor.com)

    - BlowFish encryption code by Bruse Schneier (http://www.schneier.com/blowfish.html)
    - The Secure Hash Algtorithm by the National Security Agency (http://www.w3.org/PICS/DSig/SHA1_1_0.html)

    - Crystal icons by Everaldo (http://www.everaldo.com/crystal.html)

    - Requesters pics by AlieM

@EndNode

@Node "Usage" "Ling - Usage"

  @{b}Usage@{ub}


    First of all you must create a Ling database.

    Press the Create gadget or select the Create menu item.

    An ASL requester will be popup so that you may select a
    file name for the database to be created.

    After you have selected the file name, a password requester
    will appear to let you define the database password.

    A robust password should consist in mixed
    uppercase/lowercase/digits min 6 character long string.

    That is because BlowFish CBC encryption is craccable by
    brute force if its possword is weak.

    Now Ling is ready to store your accounts.

@EndNode

