@Node "Bar" "Ling - Bar"

  @{b}Bar@{ub}


    This the the tool bar of Ling.
    You may configure it in MUI Settings/TheBar.

@EndNode

@Node "PassList" "Ling - Accounts list"

  @{b}Accounts list@{ub}


    This the the accounts list.

    If you choosed to show passwords in list, each entry consists of:

    Name - User- Password - Note

    otherwise it consists of:

    Name - User- Note

    I suggest to not show passwords in list.

    Note that Ling exposes the database password only for the
    time needed (it is when checking the password and when
    loading/saving a database); database and accounts
    passwords are stored in memory in encrypted form: a simple
    brute force search in memory will not reveal them.

    The list has an useful context menu.

@EndNode

@Node "Edit" "Ling - Edit"

  @{b}Edit@{ub}


    This is the edit accounts window.

    If you choosed to show passwords in edit, you see the
    password of the account. I suggest to not show passwords
    in list and neither in edit.

    The Gen gadget opens the Passwords generator window, if
    you wish to create a new brand password for the account.

@EndNode

@Node "PassReq" "Ling - Password requester"

  @{b}Password requester@{ub}


    This is the Password requester window.

    It is used to input a database name to open/save and its
    password.

@EndNode

@Node "Search" "Ling - Search window"

  @{b}Search window@{ub}


    This is the Search window.

    You simply input an AmigaDOS pattern and search for it.
    If you enabled passwords in list, they are explored as
    well, otherwise they are not.

@EndNode

@Node "GenPass" "Ling - Passwords generator"

  @{b}Passwords generator@{ub}


    This is the Passwords generator window, useful when you need
    to create a password on the fly.

@EndNode

@Node "Prefs" "Ling - Preferences window"

  @{b}Preferences window@{ub}


    This is Ling Preferences windows:

    o Options
      General options

      - On double click
        The action to perform when the user double-clicks on an
        entry

      - Show passwords in list
        If selected, passwords are shown in list

      - Show passwords in edit
        If selected, password is shown in edit window

      - Save db on every change
        If selected, current database is saved on every change

    o Passwords
      Passwords policy

      - Passwords length
        The length of the passwords generated by the passwords
        generator

      - Use lowercase letters
        Include lowercase letters in passwords

      - Use UPPERCASE letters
        Include UPPERCASE letters in passwords

      - Use digits
        Include decimal digits in passwords

      - Use symbols
        Include symbols (f.e. %, &, #) in passwords

      - Only readable characters
        Only use easy to read character in passwords (f.e. 0 and
        O are not used)

      - Use only hexadecimal digits
        Only use 0-9 and a-f in passwords

    o Security
      Security options

      - Quit timeout

        Define the minutes of inactivity after which Ling is
        quit; inactivity means you didn't do anything (moving
        the mouse within a Ling windows is not considered
        activity) (bug or maybe feature: activity on MUI
        settings window is ignored)

      - Clear clipboard on exit
        Clear clipboard when Ling is quit

@EndNode

@Node "Menus" "Ling - Menus"

  @{b}Menus@{ub}


    o Project

      - About
        Open the about window

      - About MUI
        Open the About MUI window

      - Hide
        Iconify Ling

      - Quit
        Quit Ling

    o Database

      - Create
        Create a new Ling database

      - Open
        Open a Ling database

      - Save
        Save the current database

      - Save as
        Save the current database with a new name

      - Change password
        Change current database password

      - Add
        Add an account

      - Edit
        Edit the active account

      - Remove
        Remove the active account

      - Copy user
        Copy the user of the active account to the clipbaord

      - Copy pass
        Copy the pass of the active account to the clipbaord

      - Clear clip
        Clear the clipboard

      - Export to CSV
        Exports current db in CSV format (bug: note are ignored)

      - Import from CSV
        Import data froma a CSV file

      - Generate passwords
        Open the Passwords generator window

    o Preferences

      - Edit
        Open the Preferences window

      - MUI
        Open the MUI Settings window

@EndNode

@Node "Changes" "Ling - Changes"

  @{b}Changes@{ub}

    o Ling 1.5
      - Added search stuff
      - Some bugs fixed
      - Made compilable under SAS-C

    o Ling 1.4
      - TheBar is now draggable
      - Minor debugging
      - CVS i/o now saves notes, but I was too lazy to
        write serious routines :)
      - Some minor changes


    o Ling 1.3
      Windows were left locked after an export operation


    o Ling 1.2

      - Arggggggg found a very bad bad in passwords saving
        All 1.1 archive are not compatible anymore
      - Many other changes


    o Ling 1.1

      - Changed RNG function: now it is a KISS one with
        a sha1-ed randomly generated seed

      - Some minor change


    o Ling 1.0
      First public release

@EndNode

